<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-08-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-08-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="747" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d747">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">701.0090/1756a: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-08-11">August 11,
                                        1943</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1924. American interests—Japan. Your 4695, August 3. Department, as
                                stated in its 1739 July 24, hopes that some at least of the
                                civilians from Guam may be repatriated on the next exchange. To the
                                extent that this may not be feasible, Department is willing that
                                Swiss representative list other eligible Americans for inclusion in
                                the exchange.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>